From 59313a2cc9a45b3300ea88e737fd129b15786ced Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Priyadarshnee Srinivasan <priys@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Jun 2025 14:58:29 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL wifi:ath12k: Handle switch to LPI and
 invalid payload

Currently, when the AFC server becomes unreachable, the firmware continues
using the previously provisioned AFC payload and remains in standard power
mode for the duration of the grace period. This has a problem where the
system does not proactively transition to low power mode or notify user
space until the grace period expires.

To address this issue, handle the SWITCH_TO_LPI event from
HALPHY by clearing the current AFC payload in the driver and notifying user
space through a vendor NL event. Mark all standard power regulatory rules
in the current regulatory domain as NO_IR to indicate that standard power
transmission is no longer permitted.

Also handle invalid AFC payloads received from firmware. If the payload
is empty or the AFC power event indicates failure, clear the existing
payload and apply the same actions as for the SWITCH_TO_LPI event.

These changes ensure that user space applications are informed of
AFC fallback conditions and can respond appropriately by clearing their
payloads and switching to the lowest or best available power mode. If no
valid channels are found, applications are expected to
bring down the 6 GHz link.

